{
  "texts": [
    "ACOSQE is challenged not only by the scarcity and diversity of datasets but also by the ambiguity, implicitness, and complexity of aspects and opinions and the relationships and consistency among quadruples.",
    "Ambiguity arises when the same word or phrase can convey different meanings or sentiments depending on the context or domain.",
    "For example, \"small\" may be positive or negative for different products or attributes.",
    "Implicitness and complexity occur when some aspects or opinions are not explicitly mentioned in the sentence and require common sense or background knowledge to infer.",
    "For example, \"this restaurant is clean\" suggests the aspect of \"service\" and the opinion of \"good,\" but they are not overtly expressed."
  ]
}